==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Medlar
<hw>Med"lar</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[OE. <ets>medler</ets>
medlar tree, OF. <ets>meslier</ets>, F. <ets>n⟦eacute⟧flier</ets>, L.
<ets>mespilum</ets>, <ets>mespilus</ets>, Gr. <?/, <?/. Cf.
<er>Naseberry</er>.]</ety> <def>A tree of the genus <gen>Mespilus</gen>
(<spn>Mespilus Germanica</spn>); also, the fruit of the tree. The fruit
is something like a small apple, but has a bony endocarp. When first
gathered the flesh is hard and austere, and it is not eaten until it has
begun to decay.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><cs><col><b>Japan medlar</b></col> <fld>(Bot.)</fld>, <cd>the loquat.
See <er>Loquat</er>.</cd> -- <col><b>Neapolitan medlar</b></col>
<fld>(Bot.)</fld>, <cd>a kind of thorn tree (<spn>Crataegus
Azarolus</spn>); also, its fruit.</cd></cs>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Medle</ent>⟦br⟧
